sec.p:
This raises a question: how to minimize Landau-Zener transitions and go deeper into the energy landscape of the spin glass. Recently, an iterative cyclic quantum annealing algorithm43 has been proposed. In this paper we demonstrate that the key elements of this algorithm—the reference Hamiltonian43–46 and cycling through the many-body localization transition47–49—are indeed useful steps towards improved quantum optimization routines. These elements, used together, allow for the manipulation of the spin-glass energy landscape, effectively reducing the number of Landau-Zener transitions and facilitating a deeper exploration of low-energy states.Figure 1
